originalText.text: the woman at the register purposely decided to pack up boxes while i was waiting on line to pickup my package. my package was also ripped open. thankfully nothing was missing. this place has to do better. this service is very convenient and there is people like that out there that ruin it for everyone else.

originalText.text:
Usually I order to my home address but since most of the products I order is for work and my job is nearby I figured I’ll try it out since my supervisor frowns upon employees ordering packages to job locations as previously a employee was busted by feds ordering painkillers from a shady Canadian online pharmacy.

Anyway, first time; my package said that it was inside the locker and after opening I found nothing inside! Took 3 months of numerous complaints and phone calls and emails to even have an investigation going that to this day is still pending.

Second and last time; apparently someone managed to gain access and open the locker and take my package. I do t know if it’s a Whole Foods employee, the delivery person or a thief who somehow knows to get into these things. Filed a police report month ago and detectives assigned must be one of those cops who is on modified duty due to something she had done.

She keeps telling me that she’s working with the postal police and whole food supervisor to figure out and the last email from her was half a month ago.

I’ll stick with shipping my packages to my house.

Thanks for trying Amazon!
